<paragraph blockId="5.[811,1457,1746,2028]" box="[813,957,1746,1772]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[811,1457,1746,2028]" lastBlockId="7.[130,777,215,560]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Diffuse, loosely spreading herb; branches filiform, sometimes slightly angular, glabrous, 
<quantity box="[1074,1146,1809,1836]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="cm" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5-8 cm</quantity>
long.Leaves opposite, spreading along the main axis; rosette leaves lacking; lower cauline leaves 
<quantity box="[881,969,1874,1900]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="4.0">4-9 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1038,1167,1874,1900]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.4">0.4-0.7 mm</quantity>
wide; upper cauline leaves 
<quantity box="[813,898,1905,1932]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6-7 mm</quantity>
long, (0.3) 
<quantity box="[1015,1119,1905,1932]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5-1 mm</quantity>
wide; leaves sessile, blade basally connate forming a shallow, scarious cup; apex mucronate; blade glabrous. Inflorescence single-flowered, pedicel filiform, 
<emphasis box="[811,828,2002,2027]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">c.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[834,934,2001,2028]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8-10 mm</quantity>
long, upright, glabrous. Flowers bisexual, paired, terminal or axillary, bracts paired, foliaceous, 
<emphasis box="[608,624,216,241]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">c.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[631,715,215,242]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
long. Calyx cymbiform, sepals 4 or rarely 5, ovate, apex acute to obtuse, 
<quantity box="[215,341,279,306]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="1.7" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.6">1.6-1.8 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous, margin hyaline, appressed at the time of capsule maturity. Petals 4 or 5, alternisepalous, ovate to elliptic, apex acute to obtuse, 
<quantity box="[535,663,343,369]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="1.2999999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.2">1.2-1.4 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.499999999999999" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="0.6499999999999999" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.6">0.6- 0.7 mm</quantity>
wide, thin, hyaline. Stamens (4)5(6), episepalous; filament 
<quantity box="[229,358,407,433]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="1.2999999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.2">1.2-1.4 mm</quantity>
long, slightly enlarged toward the base, anthers dorsifixed.Pistil ovoid, 
<emphasis box="[453,470,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">c.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[476,559,438,465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long, stigmatic lobes as many as sepals. Fruit capsule, opening lengthwise by 4 or rarely 5 valves, opposite to sepals, 
<quantity box="[505,636,502,529]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="2.6" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.5">2.5-2.7 mm</quantity>
long, longer than sepals. Seeds reniform, dark brown.
</paragraph>
